[{"question":"How do you actually pronounce your name?","answer":"Charlize Theron.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":28,"aSentId":29},{"question":"What is the correct South African, dare I say it, African way of pronouncing this?","answer":"Charlize Theron.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":34,"aSentId":35},{"question":"And you quite consciously went and taught yourself how to speak in an American accent, right?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":43,"aSentId":44},{"question":"Do you speak African certainly?","answer":"Every day.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":49,"aSentId":50},{"question":"Can you speak African to her?","answer":"Oh, yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":52,"aSentId":53},{"question":"So you speak it completely fluently?","answer":"Oh, I think more fluently than I speak English.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"Woody?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":68,"aSentId":69},{"question":"Guilty as charged?","answer":"None of this -- there\u0027s no truth to it whatsoever.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":73,"aSentId":74},{"question":"But he calls you Chuck?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":87,"aSentId":88},{"question":"Heading that way?","answer":"Because I want to actually work until I\u0027m 108 and I don\u0027t think you can\u0027t have longevity if you just kind of fall back on one aspect of what you are.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":105,"aSentId":106},{"question":"There\u0027s never the safe one, is there?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t think human beings are -- I think we\u0027re pretty complicated.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":112,"aSentId":113},{"question":"Oh, dear God, what is this, an hour show?","answer":"Yes, we got plenty of time, seriously.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":126,"aSentId":127},{"question":"Do you really love the aging process?","answer":"So far, I said.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"Is that because it\u0027s obviously treating you quite well?","answer":"Look, I\u0027m only 35.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":138,"aSentId":139},{"question":"So you get to these random houses, and what do you do?","answer":"I -- the first thing I do is I inspect every closet and drawer.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":164,"aSentId":165},{"question":"There are guys going to say who is this weirdo?","answer":"Exactly.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":177,"aSentId":178},{"question":"It\u0027s fascinating watching you because I know you don\u0027t like watching yourself, do you?","answer":"I\u0027ve gotten a lot better.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":189,"aSentId":190},{"question":"Do you know how much money you\u0027ve taken at the box office in movies you\u0027ve been in?","answer":"God, no.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":216,"aSentId":217},{"question":"That\u0027s not bad, is it?","answer":"That sounds good.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":220,"aSentId":221},{"question":"You don\u0027t care how much they make, these films?","answer":"I care.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":227,"aSentId":228},{"question":"Which one would you prefer at this stage of your career?","answer":"HERON: I guess I would take the one that makes the billion dollars, but the critics don\u0027t care for it because then I can go make seven of the ones that I love.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":238,"aSentId":239},{"question":"Hey, Todd, do we even have factory work?","answer":"I\u0027m sorry.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":260,"aSentId":261},{"question":"I mean, when you look back on it now, obviously brilliant for you in your career -- but to actually play that role, what was the experience like?","answer":"That was the greatest gift I think I\u0027ve ever been given in my career.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":270,"aSentId":271},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Yes, look, it\u0027s absolutely amazing to win an Academy Award.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"Did you watch the Oscars as a young girl?","answer":"I did, yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":275,"aSentId":276},{"question":"ORGAN: Have you met him?","answer":"Yes, yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":328,"aSentId":329},{"question":"When did you meet him?","answer":"The first time I met him, I had just won the Academy Award.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":330,"aSentId":331},{"question":"And what did he say to you?","answer":"The nicest things that any icon or hero could possibly say to you, things that I\u0027m so not deserving of.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"Like what?","answer":"Just, you know, giving me credit for being a South African and kind of putting South Africa on the map, which I didn\u0027t, but I\u0027ll take that any day from Nelson Mandela.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":336,"aSentId":337},{"question":"Any other?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":342,"aSentId":343},{"question":"Women?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":344,"aSentId":345},{"question":"Who else?","answer":"I don\u0027t know if they were women but I know another category South Africans have won.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":346,"aSentId":347},{"question":"How much of it is down to what happened, if anything?","answer":"Look, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":371,"aSentId":372},{"question":"What is the main reason do you think that it is so bad in South Africa, and what can be done to tackle it properly do you think?","answer":"I think it is a lack of education.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":444,"aSentId":445},{"question":"How do you get them?","answer":"You can go to our Web site, Charlizeafricaoutreach.org, and you can buy them there.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"And directly help?","answer":"Yes, directly -- look, here is the thing.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466},{"question":"What is the single biggest problem that the young in South Africa just don\u0027t really want to use condoms or even know much about them, is that the problem?","answer":"It is knowledge.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"What was it about the story here which grabbed your attention?","answer":"Well, I loved Tatiana\u0027s book and, you know, this is a story that is particularly relevant to me.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":516,"aSentId":517},{"question":"But where does this rank for you personally?","answer":"It really ranks with me strongly because the subject matter is so personal.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":559,"aSentId":560},{"question":"What was the thinking?","answer":"I think Kristin Scott Thomas, you know, who I first worked with on \"The English Patient\" is, you know, one of the smartest, best actresses.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":569,"aSentId":570},{"question":"And Harvey, when does the film get released here in America?","answer":"Movie opens next Friday.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":601,"aSentId":602},{"question":"I mean, did you ever meet Margaret Thatcher?","answer":"I never did, but as a liberal.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":623,"aSentId":624},{"question":"And that I think is often the greatest characteristic of any leader, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"She put her principles first.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":639,"aSentId":640},{"question":"How are your liberal friends going to react, Harvey, when you seem to be the one man who rehabilitates the Thatcher image for the world?","answer":"I\u0027m going to be run out of all my social circles, Piers.","docId":"110716pmt","qSentId":645,"aSentId":646}]